          (guru) who has realized the truth of Advaita Vedanta. Self-study without proper guidance 
          can lead to misunderstanding and intellectual confusion.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text-primary">The Guru-Shishya Parampara:</strong> 
          Traditional Vedantic knowledge is transmitted through the unbroken lineage of teacher and 
          student. A qualified guru can unfold the subtle meanings, remove doubts, and guide the 
          student systematically toward realization.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text-primary">Qualifications for Study:</strong> 
          The student should possess the four-fold qualifications (sadhana chatushtaya): discrimination 
          between eternal and non-eternal, dispassion, six virtues (mental control, sense control, 
          withdrawal, forbearance, faith, concentration), and intense desire for liberation.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm italic">
          This platform serves as a reference resource and companion to traditional study, not as a replacement 
          for the guru-shishya relationship.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

